In a real life story akin to Kevin Bacon's quest in the 1984 film Footloose, illegal dancing in the street has broken out in a Utah town as residents fight for their right to boogie.

Citizens of St George, Utah, took to the streets in a 'dance protest' after clashing with authorities over laws that require a permit to allow dancing in public.

Dancing without a permit could result in arrests for inciting a riot using laws that critics say infringe on their constitutional rights.

