The party-pooper law was highlighted last month when the town's annual Monster Mash party was raided by six police officers who informed organizers dancing was prohibited according to the fine print of the event's party permit.

Partygoers were instructed via loudspeaker there was to be no dancing.

As the other activities continued, officers stayed at the party to ensure no rebellious dancing broke out.

Now residents have taken to the streets in a protest - mirroring Kevin Bacon's character in the seminal 1980s film Footloose, in which he successfully overturns a small town's laws using the only power of dance.

Jared Keddington, the organizer of the Monster Mash event, said St George was becoming 'notorious' for its rules, ABC4 Utah reported.

